text: It was a tough month in the ratings department for CNN.According to the latest numbers from Nielsen, CNN posted 553,000 total viewers in the total day category ‚Äî down 15 percent from May 2018. MSNBC put up 912,000 viewers in that category, and Fox News posted 1,342,000. CNN did squeak by over MSNBC in the advertiser-coveted 25-54 demographic with 137,000 viewers to 134,000. But those numbers paled in comparison to Fox News ‚Äî which posted 231,000.The news didn‚Äôt get much better for CNN in primetime. The network averaged 761,000 overall viewers from 8-11 p.m. in May ‚Äî lagging well behind MSNBC (1,654,000) and Fox News (2,388,000). Worse yet, CNN also got thumped in the key demo. The network posted 185,000 in the 25-54 age bracket, trailing MSNBC‚Äôs 242,000 and Fox News‚Äôs 377,000.Individually, it was a big month for Sean Hannity. The Fox News 9 p.m. host put some distance between himself and his rival, MSNBC‚Äôs Rachel Maddow, leading all of cable news with 3,138,000 overall viewers and 506,000 in the demo. (Maddow posted 2,608,000, and 410,000 in those categories respectively.) Tucker Carlson also scored ‚Äî finishing No. 2 in cable news with 2,761,000 overall viewers, and 473,000 in the 25-54 bracket.

text: Trump is using a common authoritarian propaganda technique. He keeps things uncertain so that he can't be tied to any particular decision or worldview. text:
Yes, that phrase has been bugging me from the beginning. My thought is usually, "Just answer the damn question! Oh, that's right, you don't have a clue." Another frequent incompetence-revealing equivocation he uses is in the form of "Maybe [something] or maybe [not something]." That one grates on my nerves, too. Of course, the main characteristic of his speaking is the constant lying and misrepresentation. Recently he was asked about Iran. It seemed to me, in that three minute response to a reporter, that he couldn't go ten seconds without misrepresenting or outright lying about something.

And then there are his mindless, off-the-rails rants where he rambles from one thing to another. I have a file of several of those incoherent speeches. John Oliver compared one such speech to a cell phone's predictive text.

Okay, for your entertainment, I'll post both of them.
Here's what Trump said: 
"Look, having nuclear -- my uncle was a great professor and scientist and engineer -- Dr. John Trump at MIT; good genes, very good genes, okay? Very smart, the Wharton School of Finance, very good, very smart. You know, if you're a conservative Republican, if I were a liberal, if, like, okay, if I ran as a liberal Democrat, they would say I'm one of the smartest people anywhere in the world -- it's true! -- but when you're a conservative Republican they try -- oh, do they do a number! That's why I always start off: 'Went to Wharton, was a good student. Went there, went there, did this, built a fortune.' You know I have to give my, like, credentials all the time, because we're a little disadvantaged, but you look at the nuclear deal, the thing that really bothers me -- it would have been so easy, and it's not as important as these lives are, nuclear is powerful; my uncle explained that to me many, many years ago, the power, and that was 35 years ago; he would explain the power of what's going to happen and he was right -- who would've thought? We carried 600 pounds of ice, but no ice maker. We followed the birds. The Molokai channel is a desolate place, so we‚Äôd go 50 miles out. You know this part of commercial fishing. We chased the birds between Molokai and Oahu. Mahi go nuts on 9, 0 reels. Ahi take our lures and go deep in circles. Marlin decidedly wreck our gear, and we bat their heads. When you see an Ahi coming up from the depths you know that‚Äôs a thousand dollar fish. What we do is, give away our first thousand dollar fish to neighbors. It‚Äôs a good luck thing. We cut the fish in the yard, the dogs love the scraps, and our neighbors trade fish for Portuguese bean soup. We show up on the scene, the neighbors are already on the trade. That‚Äôs how we did this for years. You‚Äôre a fisherman, so you know what I‚Äôm talking about. Nice knowing you my Aussie friend. Aloha.ü§ôüèº
